section.para:
          Sometimes it is necessary to use different group
          configurations for different scenarios.  For example,
          imagine we need to test pub/sub scenario where publishers
          use websocket connections and subscribers use MQTT, or we
          want to test bridging between MQTT brokers that have
          different hostnames. It can be achieved like this:

emqttb @pub -t 'foo/%n' -g wss \
       @sub -t 'foo/#' -g mqtt \
       @g -g wss -h localhost --transport ws --ssl \
       @g -g mqtt -h localhost --transport sock
